The paper proposes a new technique for training deep neural networks using data from multiple entities in a distributed fashion. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses security concerns, which may indicate that it belongs to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the issue of computational resources, which may suggest that it belongs to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed algorithm in data-sensitive domains such as healthcare and finance, which may indicate that it belongs to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
